column1: #Text=Techtonica is a non-profit project of SocialGood that does free tech training and job placement for unemployed or underemployed folks .
#Text=For more information , please see our website : Techtonica.org
#Text=Program participants will learn to do full - stack web development using JavaScript .
#Text=What bootcamps and Techtonica have in common is the fact that they are intensive training .
#Text=However , bootcamps can be pretty passive classroom learning and they cost $ 15,000 + for the students .

#Text=Techtonica aims to be more like the workplace to make the transition into the industry better — instead of having an instructor constantly guiding you ( which you wo n’t have in any software engineering job ) , you are given a general schedule of topics and assignments ( see our curriculum repo for an idea of the resources provided ) and you ’re expected to figure out what to do on your own or in collaboration with volunteers , mentors , tech groups , and other participants .
#Text=We ’re making Techtonica ’s program as hands - on and project - based as possible to best prepare you for work in tech .
#Text=The following is the approximate sequence of the topics during the program but is always being tuned and optimized so if you have questions , please open an issue .
#Text=Before beginning the program , participants meet weekly for 4 weeks to learn JavaScript fundamentals .
#Text=Participants should memorize common JavaScript built - in functions within the first month .
#Text=6. Intro to Command Line Interface Tools
#Text=20. One of either : Living in Open Workspaces or Working Remotely depending on program status .
#Text=7. Article : What Exactly is the DOM ?
#Text=8. How the Internet Works ( The Other Kind of Networking )
#Text=23. Deploy your Portfolio Project : Deploying Client - Side Apps with Netlify

#Text=After Week 14 , Participants build a full - stack web application in the course of one month , from inception to production .
#Text=Creating project planning docs with wire frames
